<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,724,1270]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
DIAGNOSIS. This species is distinguished from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chillcott, 1983:" authorityYear="1306" box="[1075,1243,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chaetodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1075,1243,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Chaetodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the eyes being narrowly separated (not contiguous) on the face and the hind tibia lacking anterodorsal bristles (
<figureCitation box="[516,586,804,830]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[264,367,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[272,1307,1329,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-295@4.[272,1331,1329,1812]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chaetodromia pulchra sp. nov. A. habitus, lateral view. B. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. (specimen B­8425­148)." pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,724,1270]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
DESCRIPTION. Female (
<figureCitation box="[619,711,844,870]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[264,367,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[272,1307,1329,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-295@4.[272,1331,1329,1812]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chaetodromia pulchra sp. nov. A. habitus, lateral view. B. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. (specimen B­8425­148)." pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Length 
<quantity box="[823,931,844,870]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.39" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.39">1.39 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[942,1006,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Head</emphasis>
. Ground colour dark. Eyes apparently lacking ommatrichia (pubescence); narrowly separated below antennae; facets not noticeably enlarged below antennae. Frons evenly divergent. Two pairs of ocellar bristles; anterior pair convergent, inserted between median and posterior ocelli and broadly separated; posterior pair inserted anterior to posterior ocelli. One pair of divergent and one pair of convergent vertical bristles present, the latter inserted outside divergent pair so that pair on each side appear cruciate. Antennae arising about middle of head; scape small, shorter than half length of pedicel; pedicel globose, two­thirds as long as postpedicel, lacking long ventral preapical bristle; postpedicel short­conical, with terminal arista­like style; latter subequal to height of head; antennal segments concolorous (brown). Palpus ovate with long, apical setula.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="4" pageNumber="41" startId="4.[264,367,1838,1862]" targetBox="[272,1307,1329,1812]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,1838,1896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,394,1838,1862]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Solórzano Kraemer &amp; Sinclair &amp; Cumming, 2005" authorityName="Solórzano Kraemer &amp; Sinclair &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2005" box="[401,644,1839,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chaetodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[401,644,1839,1862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Chaetodromia pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[651,734,1838,1861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[740,759,1838,1862]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
. habitus, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1000,1018,1838,1862]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">B</emphasis>
. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. (specimen B­8425­148).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,284,1278]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,396,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Thorax</emphasis>
. Ground colour dark. Scutum entirely clothed in dense microtrichia. Postpronotal lobe small; 1 pprn; acr developed, but not clearly visible; at least 3 pairs of dc; 1 spal; 1 pal; 1 pair of sctl.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,284,1278]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,372,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Wing</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[396,486,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[264,367,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[272,1307,1329,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-295@4.[272,1331,1329,1812]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chaetodromia pulchra sp. nov. A. habitus, lateral view. B. wing, Scale 0.5 mm. (specimen B­8425­148)." pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) Length ca 
<quantity box="[629,722,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
. Broad with blunt­tip; hyaline; microtrichia evenly distributed; costal setulae normally developed; Rs more than one­half length of cell bm; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[284,314,496,513]" fontSize="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">2+3</subScript>
slightly arched, extending to about apical quarter of wing; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1025,1055,496,513]" fontSize="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">4+5</subScript>
gently arched, slightly divergent from M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[475,505,539,556]" fontSize="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">1+2</subScript>
; cell br subequal in length to cell bm; crossvein bm­cu nearly transverse; A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[363,373,582,599]" fontSize="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">1</subScript>
present as faint fold. Knob of halter dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,284,1278]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,367,612,637]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Legs</emphasis>
. All segments mostly straight, except hind femur slightly curved medially. Fore femur moderately thickened. Mid femur with 1 outstanding preapical anterior bristle and several preapical anteroventral bristles. Hind femur with several preapical posteroventral bristles. Hind tibia without anterodorsal bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1323,284,1278]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,422,772,797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Segments uniformly telescopic with first 5 segments broadly inflated compared to posterior segments, lacking distinctive bristles. Terminalia: sternite 8 entire, not partially separated, dorsal margin straight; cercus short, ovate, shorter than half­length of tergite 8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
